===English===
===Pronunciation===
'''fire*de*part*ment'''

===Etymology===
[[fire]] + [[department]]

This term refers to an organization dedicated to the mitigation of emergencies, particularly of fires. Today, a fire department may provide many emergency services, such as Emergency Medical Services (EMS) and various forms of technical rescue. This term is often used interchangeably with [[fire company]] but also may refer to a higher level organization. In large cities, single firefighting units are usually referred to as companies, while the organization as a whole is the fire department.

